----------------------------程序运行时长: 0.00 秒，开始运行第 1 个问题--------------------------------
A factory produces two types of food, I and II, and currently has 50 skilled workers. It is known that one skilled worker can produce $10 \ \mathrm{kg} / \ \mathrm{h}$ of food I or $6 \ \mathrm{kg} / \ \mathrm{h}$ of food II. According to contract bookings, the weekly demand for these two foods will rise sharply, as shown in Table 1-11. Therefore, the factory has decided to train 50 new workers by the end of the 8th week. It is known that a worker works $40 \ \mathrm{h}$ per week, and a skilled worker can train up to three new workers in two weeks (during the training period, both the skilled worker and the trainees do not participate in production). The weekly wage of a skilled worker is 360 yuan, the weekly wage of a trainee during the training period is 120 yuan, and after training, the wage is 240 yuan per week, with the same production efficiency as skilled workers. During the transition period of training, many skilled workers are willing to work overtime, and the factory has decided to arrange some workers to work $60 \ \mathrm{h}$ per week, with a weekly wage of 540 yuan. If the booked food cannot be delivered on time, the compensation fee for each week of delay per $ \ \mathrm{kg}$ is 0.5 yuan for food I and 0.6 yuan for food II. Under these conditions, how should the factory make comprehensive arrangements to minimize the total cost?

Table 1-11

| Week | 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6 | 7 | 8 |
|------|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| I    | 10000 | 10000  | 12000  | 12000  | 16000  | 16000  | 20000  | 20000  |
| II   | 6000 | 7200 | 8400 | 10800 | 10800 | 12000  | 12000  | 12000  |
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# -----------------------------
# Data
# -----------------------------
weeks = range(1, 9)

demand_I = {
    1:10000, 2:10000, 3:12000, 4:12000,
    5:16000, 6:16000, 7:20000, 8:20000
}

demand_II = {
    1:6000, 2:7200, 3:8400, 4:10800,
    5:10800, 6:12000, 7:12000, 8:12000
}

initial_skilled = 50
required_new_workers = 50

# Productivity per worker per week
cap_I_regular = 10 * 40   # 400
cap_II_regular = 6 * 40   # 240
cap_I_overtime = 10 * 60  # 600
cap_II_overtime = 6 * 60  # 360

# Costs
wage_regular = 360
wage_overtime = 540
wage_trainee = 120
penalty_I = 0.5
penalty_II = 0.6

# -----------------------------
# Model
# -----------------------------
m = gp.Model("Factory_Planning")

# Decision variables
T = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="TrainStart")          # trainees starting
R = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="TrainersStart")       # trainers starting
OT = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="OvertimeWorkers")

S = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="AvailableSkilled")
TotalSkill = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="TotalSkilled")

xI_reg = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Prod_I_Reg")
xII_reg = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Prod_II_Reg")
xI_ot = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Prod_I_OT")
xII_ot = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Prod_II_OT")

backlog_I = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Backlog_I")
backlog_II = m.addVars(weeks, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Backlog_II")

# -----------------------------
# Constraints
# -----------------------------

for w in weeks:
    # Trainers capacity: 1 trainer trains up to 3 trainees
    m.addConstr(T[w] <= 3 * R[w])

    # Compute completed trainees
    completed = T[w-2] if w-2 >= 1 else 0

    # Total skilled workers available in system
    if w == 1:
        m.addConstr(TotalSkill[w] == initial_skilled)
    else:
        m.addConstr(TotalSkill[w] == TotalSkill[w-1] + completed)

    # Skilled workers unavailable due to training
    trainers_busy = R[w]
    if w-1 >= 1:
        trainers_busy += R[w-1]

    # Available skilled for production
    m.addConstr(S[w] == TotalSkill[w] - trainers_busy)

    # Overtime workers cannot exceed available skilled
    m.addConstr(OT[w] <= S[w])

    # Production capacity constraints
    m.addConstr(xI_reg[w] + xII_reg[w] <= cap_I_regular * (S[w] - OT[w]))
    m.addConstr(xI_ot[w] + xII_ot[w] <= cap_I_overtime * OT[w])

    # Backlog balance for product I
    if w == 1:
        m.addConstr(backlog_I[w] == demand_I[w] - (xI_reg[w] + xI_ot[w]))
    else:
        m.addConstr(backlog_I[w] == backlog_I[w-1] + demand_I[w] - (xI_reg[w] + xI_ot[w]))

    # Backlog balance for product II
    if w == 1:
        m.addConstr(backlog_II[w] == demand_II[w] - (xII_reg[w] + xII_ot[w]))
    else:
        m.addConstr(backlog_II[w] == backlog_II[w-1] + demand_II[w] - (xII_reg[w] + xII_ot[w]))

# Total trainees trained equals 50
m.addConstr(gp.quicksum(T[w] for w in weeks) == required_new_workers)

# Non-negativity for backlog
for w in weeks:
    m.addConstr(backlog_I[w] >= 0)
    m.addConstr(backlog_II[w] >= 0)

# -----------------------------
# Objective Function
# -----------------------------
total_cost = gp.quicksum(
    wage_regular * (TotalSkill[w] - OT[w]) +
    wage_overtime * OT[w] +
    wage_trainee * (T[w] + (T[w-1] if w-1 >= 1 else 0)) +
    penalty_I * backlog_I[w] +
    penalty_II * backlog_II[w]
    for w in weeks
)

m.setObjective(total_cost, GRB.MINIMIZE)

# -----------------------------
# Solve
# -----------------------------
m.optimize()

# -----------------------------
# Output Results
# -----------------------------
if m.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Cost: {m.objVal:.2f}\n")
    for w in weeks:
        print(f"Week {w}:")
        print(f"  Train Start: {T[w].x:.0f}")
        print(f"  Trainers Start: {R[w].x:.0f}")
        print(f"  Available Skilled: {S[w].x:.2f}")
        print(f"  Overtime Workers: {OT[w].x:.0f}")
        print(f"  Production I: {(xI_reg[w].x + xI_ot[w].x):.2f}")
        print(f"  Production II: {(xII_reg[w].x + xII_ot[w].x):.2f}")
        print(f"  Backlog I: {backlog_I[w].x:.2f}")
        print(f"  Backlog II: {backlog_II[w].x:.2f}")
        print()
```
