Mary is planning her dinner tonight. Every 100 grams of okra contains 3.2 grams of fiber, every 100 grams of carrots contains 2.7 grams of fiber, every 100 grams of celery contains 1.6 grams of fiber, and every 100 grams of cabbage contains 2 grams of fiber. How many grams of each type of food should Mary buy to maximize her fiber intake?

She is considering choosing one among salmon, beef, and pork as a protein source.

She also considers choosing at least two kinds of vegetables among okra, carrots, celery, and cabbage.

The price of salmon is $4 per 100 grams, beef is $3.6 per 100 grams, pork is $1.8 per 100 grams. The price of okra is $2.6 per 100 grams, carrots are $1.2 per 100 grams, celery is $1.6 per 100 grams, and cabbage is $2.3 per 100 grams. Mary has a budget of $15 for this meal.

The total food intake should be 600 grams.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Mary_Dinner_Optimization")

# Continuous variables (grams of each food)
salmon = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="salmon")
beef = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="beef")
pork = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="pork")

okra = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="okra")
carrots = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="carrots")
celery = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="celery")
cabbage = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=600, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="cabbage")

# Binary variables for selection
y_salmon = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="y_salmon")
y_beef = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="y_beef")
y_pork = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="y_pork")

z_okra = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="z_okra")
z_carrots = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="z_carrots")
z_celery = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="z_celery")
z_cabbage = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="z_cabbage")

# Objective: Maximize fiber intake (grams)
model.setObjective(
    0.032 * okra +
    0.027 * carrots +
    0.016 * celery +
    0.020 * cabbage,
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Total food intake = 600 grams
model.addConstr(
    salmon + beef + pork +
    okra + carrots + celery + cabbage == 600,
    name="Total_Weight"
)

# Budget constraint (prices per gram)
model.addConstr(
    0.04 * salmon + 0.036 * beef + 0.018 * pork +
    0.026 * okra + 0.012 * carrots + 0.016 * celery + 0.023 * cabbage
    <= 15,
    name="Budget"
)

# Exactly one protein selected
model.addConstr(y_salmon + y_beef + y_pork == 1, name="One_Protein")

# At least two vegetables selected
model.addConstr(z_okra + z_carrots + z_celery + z_cabbage >= 2, name="At_Least_Two_Veg")

# Linking constraints (Big-M = 600)
M = 600
model.addConstr(salmon <= M * y_salmon)
model.addConstr(beef <= M * y_beef)
model.addConstr(pork <= M * y_pork)

model.addConstr(okra <= M * z_okra)
model.addConstr(carrots <= M * z_carrots)
model.addConstr(celery <= M * z_celery)
model.addConstr(cabbage <= M * z_cabbage)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Solution:")
    for v in model.getVars():
        if v.x > 1e-6:
            print(f"{v.varName}: {v.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Maximum Fiber Intake: {model.objVal:.2f} grams")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
