A company plans to produce 3 types of products $A_{1}, A_{2}, A_{3}$. It can produce for 22 days in a month. The following table gives the maximum demand (unit $=100 \mathrm{~kg}$), price ($\$ / 100 \mathrm{Kg}$), production cost (per 100Kg product), and production quota (the maximum number of 100kg units that can be produced in one day if all production lines are devoted to this product).

| Product | $A_{1}$ | $A_{2}$ | $A_{3}$ |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Maximum Demand | 5300 | 4500 | 5400 |
| Selling Price | $124$ | $109$ | $115$ |
| Production Cost | $73.30$ | $52.90$ | $65.40$ |
| Production Quota | 500 | 450 | 550 |

The fixed activation cost of the production line is as follows:

| Product | $A_{1}$ | $A_{2}$ | $A_{3}$ |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Activation Cost | $170000$ | $150000$ | $100000$ |

Minimum production batch:

$$
\begin{array}{c|ccc}
Product & A_{1} & A_{2} & A_{3} \\
\hline
Minimum Batch & 20 & 20 & 16
\end{array}
$$

Please formulate an operations research model to determine a production plan that maximizes total revenue while accommodating fixed activation costs and minimum production batch constraints.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB, quicksum

# Data
products = ['A1', 'A2', 'A3']

max_demand = {'A1': 5300, 'A2': 4500, 'A3': 5400}
price = {'A1': 124, 'A2': 109, 'A3': 115}
cost = {'A1': 73.30, 'A2': 52.90, 'A3': 65.40}
quota = {'A1': 500, 'A2': 450, 'A3': 550}  # units per day (100kg units)
activation_cost = {'A1': 170000, 'A2': 150000, 'A3': 100000}
min_batch = {'A1': 20, 'A2': 20, 'A3': 16}

total_days = 22

# Model
model = Model("Production_Planning")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(products, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Production")  # production quantity (100kg units)
y = model.addVars(products, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Activate")        # activation decision

# Objective: Maximize total profit
model.setObjective(
    quicksum((price[p] - cost[p]) * x[p] - activation_cost[p] * y[p] for p in products),
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Constraints

# Demand constraint
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(x[p] <= max_demand[p], name=f"Demand_{p}")

# Capacity constraint (total available production days)
model.addConstr(
    quicksum(x[p] / quota[p] for p in products) <= total_days,
    name="Total_Days"
)

# Activation and minimum batch constraints
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(x[p] <= max_demand[p] * y[p], name=f"Activation_UB_{p}")
    model.addConstr(x[p] >= min_batch[p] * y[p], name=f"MinBatch_{p}")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Profit: {model.objVal:.2f}")
    for p in products:
        print(f"{p}: Production = {x[p].x:.2f} (100kg units), Activated = {int(y[p].x)}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
