Hongdou Clothing Factory uses three special equipment to produce shirts, short-sleeved shirts, and casual clothes respectively. It is known that the labor, material usage, selling price, and variable cost of each of the above products are as shown in Table 5-10.

Table 5-10

| Product Name | Labor per unit | Material per unit | Selling Price | Variable Cost |
|--------------|----------------|------------------|---------------|---------------|
| Shirt        | 3              | 4                | 120           | 60            |
| Short-sleeve | 2              | 3                | 80            | 40            |
| Casual Cloth | 6              | 6                | 180           | 80            |

It is known that the available labor per week is 1500 units, the available material is 1600 units, and the weekly fixed costs for the three special equipment for producing shirts, short-sleeved shirts, and casual clothes are 2000, 1500, and 1000 respectively. Design a weekly production plan for the factory to maximize its profit.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Hongdou_Clothing_Production")

# Parameters
labor = {'shirt': 3, 'short': 2, 'casual': 6}
material = {'shirt': 4, 'short': 3, 'casual': 6}
price = {'shirt': 120, 'short': 80, 'casual': 180}
var_cost = {'shirt': 60, 'short': 40, 'casual': 80}
fixed_cost = {'shirt': 2000, 'short': 1500, 'casual': 1000}

labor_available = 1500
material_available = 1600

products = ['shirt', 'short', 'casual']

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(products, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Production", lb=0)
y = model.addVars(products, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="UseEquipment")

# Big-M values (maximum possible production limited by resources)
M = {}
for p in products:
    max_by_labor = labor_available / labor[p]
    max_by_material = material_available / material[p]
    M[p] = min(max_by_labor, max_by_material)

# Objective function: Maximize profit
model.setObjective(
    sum((price[p] - var_cost[p]) * x[p] - fixed_cost[p] * y[p] for p in products),
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Constraints
# Resource constraints
model.addConstr(sum(labor[p] * x[p] for p in products) <= labor_available, name="LaborConstraint")
model.addConstr(sum(material[p] * x[p] for p in products) <= material_available, name="MaterialConstraint")

# Linking constraints
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(x[p] <= M[p] * y[p], name=f"Link_{p}")

# Optimize model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Weekly Production Plan:")
    for p in products:
        print(f"{p.capitalize()} Production: {x[p].x:.2f}")
        print(f"Use {p.capitalize()} Equipment: {int(y[p].x)}")
    print(f"Maximum Weekly Profit: {model.objVal:.2f}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
