An investor plans to invest 100,000 yuan, with two investment options to choose from. The first investment guarantees a return of 0.7 yuan for every 1 yuan invested after one year. The second investment guarantees a return of 2 yuan for every 1 yuan invested after two years, but the investment time must be in multiples of two years. In order to maximize the investor's earnings by the end of the third year, how should the investments be made? Formulate this as a linear programming problem.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Investment_Planning")

# Parameters
initial_fund = 100000

# Decision variables
# x1_t: amount invested in investment 1 at beginning of year t (t=0,1,2)
# x2_t: amount invested in investment 2 at beginning of year t (t=0,1)
x1_0 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x1_0")
x1_1 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x1_1")
x1_2 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x1_2")

x2_0 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x2_0")
x2_1 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x2_1")

# Cash available at beginning of each year
cash_0 = initial_fund
cash_1 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="cash_1")
cash_2 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="cash_2")
cash_3 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="cash_3")

# Constraints

# Year 0 investment constraint
model.addConstr(x1_0 + x2_0 <= cash_0, name="budget_year_0")

# Cash at beginning of year 1
model.addConstr(
    cash_1 == 1.7 * x1_0 + (cash_0 - x1_0 - x2_0),
    name="cash_balance_year_1"
)

# Year 1 investment constraint
model.addConstr(x1_1 + x2_1 <= cash_1, name="budget_year_1")

# Cash at beginning of year 2
model.addConstr(
    cash_2 == 1.7 * x1_1 + (cash_1 - x1_1 - x2_1),
    name="cash_balance_year_2"
)

# Year 2 investment constraint (only investment 1 possible)
model.addConstr(x1_2 <= cash_2, name="budget_year_2")

# Cash at beginning of year 3 (final wealth)
model.addConstr(
    cash_3 == 1.7 * x1_2 + 3 * x2_1 + (cash_2 - x1_2) + 3 * x2_0,
    name="cash_balance_year_3"
)

# Objective: maximize cash at end of year 3
model.setObjective(cash_3, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal final wealth at end of year 3: {cash_3.X:.2f} yuan")
    print("Investment decisions:")
    print(f"x1_0 = {x1_0.X:.2f}")
    print(f"x2_0 = {x2_0.X:.2f}")
    print(f"x1_1 = {x1_1.X:.2f}")
    print(f"x2_1 = {x2_1.X:.2f}")
    print(f"x1_2 = {x1_2.X:.2f}")
```
