A factory produces three types of products: I, II, and III. Each product needs to go through two processing procedures, A and B. The factory has two pieces of equipment that can complete process A, denoted as A1 and A2; it has three pieces of equipment that complete process B, denoted as B1, B2, and B3. Product I can be processed on any equipment for A and B; Product II can be processed on any A equipment but only on B1 for process B; Product III can only be processed on A2 and B2. Given the unit processing time on various machines, raw material costs, product sale prices, effective machine hours, and the costs of operating the machines at full capacity as shown in Table 1-4, the task is to arrange the optimal production plan to maximize the factory's profit.

Table 1-4
| Equipment  | Product I | Product II | Product III | Effective Machine Hours | Operating Costs at Full Capacity (Yuan) |
|------------|-----------|------------|-------------|--------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| A1         | 5         | 10         |             | 6000                     | 300                                      |
| A2         | 7         | 9          | 12          | 10000                    | 321                                      |
| B1         | 6         | 8          |             | 4000                     | 250                                      |
| B2         | 4         |            | 11          | 7000                     | 783                                      |
| B3         | 7         |            |             | 4000                     | 200                                      |
| Raw Material Cost (Yuan/Unit) | 0.25 | 0.35       | 0.50       |                          |                                          |
| Unit Price (Yuan/Unit)        | 1.25 | 2.00       | 2.80       |                          |                                          |
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Sets
products = ['I', 'II', 'III']
A_machines = ['A1', 'A2']
B_machines = ['B1', 'B2', 'B3']
machines = A_machines + B_machines

# Processing time (hours per unit)
proc_time = {
    ('A1', 'I'): 5, ('A1', 'II'): 10,
    ('A2', 'I'): 7, ('A2', 'II'): 9, ('A2', 'III'): 12,
    ('B1', 'I'): 6, ('B1', 'II'): 8,
    ('B2', 'I'): 4, ('B2', 'III'): 11,
    ('B3', 'I'): 7
}

# Effective machine hours
capacity = {
    'A1': 6000,
    'A2': 10000,
    'B1': 4000,
    'B2': 7000,
    'B3': 4000
}

# Operating cost at full capacity
full_cost = {
    'A1': 300,
    'A2': 321,
    'B1': 250,
    'B2': 783,
    'B3': 200
}

# Cost per hour
cost_per_hour = {m: full_cost[m] / capacity[m] for m in machines}

# Raw material cost and selling price
raw_cost = {'I': 0.25, 'II': 0.35, 'III': 0.50}
price = {'I': 1.25, 'II': 2.00, 'III': 2.80}

# Model
model = gp.Model("Factory_Production_Planning")

# Decision variables: units processed of product p on machine m
x = model.addVars(proc_time.keys(), name="x", lb=0)

# Production quantity variables
q = model.addVars(products, name="q", lb=0)

# Flow balance constraints for process A
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[m, p] for m in A_machines if (m, p) in proc_time) == q[p],
        name=f"Flow_A_{p}"
    )

# Flow balance constraints for process B
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[m, p] for m in B_machines if (m, p) in proc_time) == q[p],
        name=f"Flow_B_{p}"
    )

# Machine capacity constraints
for m in machines:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(proc_time[m, p] * x[m, p] 
                    for p in products if (m, p) in proc_time) <= capacity[m],
        name=f"Capacity_{m}"
    )

# Objective: Maximize profit
revenue = gp.quicksum(price[p] * q[p] for p in products)
material_cost = gp.quicksum(raw_cost[p] * q[p] for p in products)
operating_cost = gp.quicksum(
    cost_per_hour[m] * gp.quicksum(proc_time[m, p] * x[m, p] 
                                   for p in products if (m, p) in proc_time)
    for m in machines
)

model.setObjective(revenue - material_cost - operating_cost, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Solve
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Profit: {model.objVal:.4f}")
    for p in products:
        print(f"Production of Product {p}: {q[p].x:.4f}")
    for (m, p) in proc_time:
        if x[m, p].x > 1e-6:
            print(f"Units of Product {p} processed on {m}: {x[m, p].x:.4f}")
