The independent country of Carelland mainly exports four commodities: steel, engines, electronic components, and plastic. Carelland's Minister of Finance (i.e., Minister of Economy) wants to maximize exports and minimize imports. The unit prices of steel, engines, electronics, and plastic on the world market are, in local currency (Klunz), 500, 1500, 300, 1200 respectively. Producing 1 unit of steel requires 0.02 units of engines, 0.01 units of plastic, 250 Klunz of other imported goods, and 6 person-months of labor. Producing 1 unit of engines requires 0.8 units of steel, 0.15 units of electronic components, 0.11 units of plastic, 300 Klunz of imported goods, and 1 person-year. One unit of electronics requires: 0.01 units of steel, 0.01 units of engines, 0.05 units of plastic, 50 Klunz of imported goods, and 6 person-months of labor. One unit of plastic requires: 0.03 units of engines, 0.2 units of steel, 0.05 units of electronic components, 300 Klunz of imported goods, and 2 person-years. Engine production is limited to 650000 units, and plastic production is limited to 60000 units. The total available labor force per year is 830000 person-months. Write a mathematical program to maximize domestic GDP and solve the problem using AMPL.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Carelland_GDP_Maximization")

# Decision variables: production quantities
steel = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Steel")
engines = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=650000, name="Engines")
electronics = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Electronics")
plastic = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=60000, name="Plastic")

# World market prices (Klunz)
price_steel = 500
price_engines = 1500
price_electronics = 300
price_plastic = 1200

# Imported goods cost per unit
import_steel = 250
import_engines = 300
import_electronics = 50
import_plastic = 300

# Labor requirements (person-months)
labor_steel = 6
labor_engines = 12  # 1 person-year = 12 months
labor_electronics = 6
labor_plastic = 24  # 2 person-years = 24 months

# Total labor available
total_labor = 830000

# Material balance constraints (production ≥ internal usage)

# Steel balance
model.addConstr(
    steel >= 0.8 * engines + 0.01 * electronics + 0.2 * plastic,
    name="Steel_Balance"
)

# Engines balance
model.addConstr(
    engines >= 0.02 * steel + 0.01 * electronics + 0.03 * plastic,
    name="Engines_Balance"
)

# Electronics balance
model.addConstr(
    electronics >= 0.15 * engines + 0.05 * plastic,
    name="Electronics_Balance"
)

# Plastic balance
model.addConstr(
    plastic >= 0.01 * steel + 0.11 * engines + 0.05 * electronics,
    name="Plastic_Balance"
)

# Labor constraint
model.addConstr(
    labor_steel * steel +
    labor_engines * engines +
    labor_electronics * electronics +
    labor_plastic * plastic
    <= total_labor,
    name="Labor_Constraint"
)

# Objective: Maximize GDP = total export value - imported goods cost
model.setObjective(
    price_steel * steel +
    price_engines * engines +
    price_electronics * electronics +
    price_plastic * plastic
    - import_steel * steel
    - import_engines * engines
    - import_electronics * electronics
    - import_plastic * plastic,
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal GDP: {model.objVal:.2f} Klunz")
    print(f"Steel Production: {steel.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Engines Production: {engines.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Electronics Production: {electronics.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Plastic Production: {plastic.x:.2f}")
