A factory produces three types of products, A, B, and C. Each unit of product A requires 1 hour for technical preparation, 10 hours of direct labor, and 3 kg of materials. Each unit of product B requires 2 hours for technical preparation, 4 hours of labor, and 2 kg of materials. Each unit of product C requires 1 hour for technical preparation, 5 hours of labor, and 1 kg of materials. The available technical preparation time is 100 hours, labor time is 700 hours, and materials are 400 kg. The company offers larger discounts for bulk purchases, as detailed in Table 1-22. Determine the company's production plan to maximize profit.
Table 1-22
| Product A       |           | Product B       |           | Product C       |           |
|:---------------|:---------:|:---------------|:---------:|:---------------|:---------:|
| Sales Volume (pieces) | Profit (yuan) | Sales Volume (pieces) | Profit (yuan) | Sales Volume (pieces) | Profit (yuan) |
| 0 ~ 40         | 10        | 0 ~ 50         | 6         | 0 ~ 100        | 5         |
| 40 ~ 100       | 9         | 50 ~ 100       | 4         | Above 100      | 4         |
| 100 ~ 150      | 8         | Above 100      | 3         |                |           |
| Above 150      | 7         |                |           |                |           |
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Production_Planning")

# -----------------------
# Segment Variables
# -----------------------

# Product A segments
A1 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=40, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="A_0_40")
A2 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=60, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="A_40_100")
A3 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=50, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="A_100_150")
A4 = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="A_above_150")

# Product B segments
B1 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=50, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="B_0_50")
B2 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=50, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="B_50_100")
B3 = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="B_above_100")

# Product C segments
C1 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=100, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="C_0_100")
C2 = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="C_above_100")

# Total production
A = A1 + A2 + A3 + A4
B = B1 + B2 + B3
C = C1 + C2

# -----------------------
# Resource Constraints
# -----------------------

# Technical preparation time
model.addConstr(1*A + 2*B + 1*C <= 100, name="Tech_Time")

# Labor time
model.addConstr(10*A + 4*B + 5*C <= 700, name="Labor_Time")

# Material constraint
model.addConstr(3*A + 2*B + 1*C <= 400, name="Material")

# -----------------------
# Objective Function
# -----------------------

profit = (
    10*A1 + 9*A2 + 8*A3 + 7*A4 +
    6*B1 + 4*B2 + 3*B3 +
    5*C1 + 4*C2
)

model.setObjective(profit, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# -----------------------
# Output Results
# -----------------------

if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Profit: {model.objVal:.2f}")
    print(f"Production Plan:")
    print(f"Product A: {A.getValue():.2f}")
    print(f"Product B: {B.getValue():.2f}")
    print(f"Product C: {C.getValue():.2f}")
