A store has formulated a purchase and sales plan for a certain product from July to December. It is known that the warehouse capacity must not exceed 500 units, with 200 units in stock at the end of June. Thereafter, purchases are made at the beginning of each month. Assume the purchase and selling prices of this product for each month are shown in Table 1-21. How much should be purchased and sold each month to maximize the total revenue?

Table 1-21
| Month | 7  | 8  | 9  | 10 | 11 | 12 |
|-------|----|----|----|----|----|----|
| Buy   | 28 | 24 | 25 | 27 | 23 | 23 |
| Sell  | 29 | 24 | 26 | 28 | 22 | 25 |
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
months = ["Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"]
buy_price = [28, 24, 25, 27, 23, 23]
sell_price = [29, 24, 26, 28, 22, 25]

initial_inventory = 200
capacity = 500
n = len(months)

# Model
model = gp.Model("Purchase_Sales_Planning")

# Decision variables
buy = model.addVars(n, lb=0, name="Buy")
sell = model.addVars(n, lb=0, name="Sell")
inventory = model.addVars(n, lb=0, ub=capacity, name="Inventory")

# Inventory balance constraints
for t in range(n):
    if t == 0:
        model.addConstr(
            inventory[t] == initial_inventory + buy[t] - sell[t],
            name=f"Inventory_Balance_{t}"
        )
    else:
        model.addConstr(
            inventory[t] == inventory[t-1] + buy[t] - sell[t],
            name=f"Inventory_Balance_{t}"
        )

# Objective: Maximize total profit
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(sell_price[t] * sell[t] - buy_price[t] * buy[t] for t in range(n)),
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Maximum Total Profit: {model.objVal:.2f}\n")
    for t in range(n):
        print(f"{months[t]}:")
        print(f"  Buy: {buy[t].x:.2f}")
        print(f"  Sell: {sell[t].x:.2f}")
        print(f"  End Inventory: {inventory[t].x:.2f}\n")
