The number of nurses required in each time period over 24 hours at a certain hospital is as follows: 2:00-6:00 - 10 people, 6:00-10:00 - 15 people, 10:00-14:00 - 25 people, 14:00-18:00 - 20 people, 18:00-22:00 - 18 people, 22:00-2:00 - 12 people. Nurses start shifts in 6 batches at 2:00, 6:00, 10:00, 14:00, 18:00, and 22:00 and work continuously for 8 hours. Please determine: If the hospital can hire contract nurses with the same working hours as regular nurses, and if the pay for regular nurses is 10 yuan/hour and for contract nurses is 15 yuan/hour, should the hospital hire contract nurses and if so, how many?
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Time periods and demand
periods = ["2-6", "6-10", "10-14", "14-18", "18-22", "22-2"]
demand = {
    "2-6": 10,
    "6-10": 15,
    "10-14": 25,
    "14-18": 20,
    "18-22": 18,
    "22-2": 12
}

# Shift start times corresponding to periods
shifts = ["2", "6", "10", "14", "18", "22"]

# Coverage matrix: each shift covers two consecutive periods (8 hours)
coverage = {
    "2": ["2-6", "6-10"],
    "6": ["6-10", "10-14"],
    "10": ["10-14", "14-18"],
    "14": ["14-18", "18-22"],
    "18": ["18-22", "22-2"],
    "22": ["22-2", "2-6"]
}

# Costs
regular_cost_per_shift = 8 * 10
contract_cost_per_shift = 8 * 15

# Create model
model = Model("Nurse_Scheduling")

# Decision variables
regular = model.addVars(shifts, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="Regular", lb=0)
contract = model.addVars(shifts, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="Contract", lb=0)

# Objective: minimize total cost
model.setObjective(
    sum(regular_cost_per_shift * regular[s] + contract_cost_per_shift * contract[s] for s in shifts),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Constraints: coverage for each period
for p in periods:
    model.addConstr(
        sum(regular[s] + contract[s] for s in shifts if p in coverage[s]) >= demand[p],
        name=f"Demand_{p}"
    )

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Minimum Total Cost: {model.objVal}")
    print("\nRegular Nurses per Shift:")
    for s in shifts:
        print(f"Start at {s}:00 -> {regular[s].x}")
    print("\nContract Nurses per Shift:")
    for s in shifts:
        print(f"Start at {s}:00 -> {contract[s].x}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
