A trading company specializes in the wholesale business of certain grains. The company currently has a warehouse with a capacity of 5000 dan. On January 1, the company has 1000 dan of grain in stock and 20,000 yuan in funds. The estimated grain prices for the first quarter are shown in Table 1-8.

Table 1-8
| Month | Purchase Price (yuan/dan) | Selling Price (yuan/dan) |
|-------|---------------------------|--------------------------|
| 1     | 2.85                      | 3.10                     |
| 2     | 3.05                      | 3.25                     |
| 3     | 2.90                      | 2.95                     |

The purchased grains will be delivered in the same month but can only be sold in the next month, and payment is required upon delivery. The company hopes to have an inventory of 2000 dan at the end of the quarter. What purchasing and selling strategy should be adopted to maximize the total profit over the three months?
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Grain_Trading_Optimization")

# Parameters
purchase_price = {1: 2.85, 2: 3.05, 3: 2.90}
selling_price = {1: 3.10, 2: 3.25, 3: 2.95}
warehouse_capacity = 5000
initial_inventory = 1000
initial_cash = 20000
final_inventory_required = 2000

# Decision variables
buy = model.addVars(1, 2, 3, name="Buy", lb=0)
sell = model.addVars(1, 2, 3, name="Sell", lb=0)
inventory = model.addVars(1, 2, 3, name="Inventory", lb=0)
cash = model.addVars(1, 2, 3, name="Cash", lb=0)

# Inventory balance constraints
model.addConstr(inventory[1] == initial_inventory - sell[1] + buy[1])
model.addConstr(inventory[2] == inventory[1] - sell[2] + buy[2])
model.addConstr(inventory[3] == inventory[2] - sell[3] + buy[3])

# Sales constraints (can only sell previous inventory)
model.addConstr(sell[1] <= initial_inventory)
model.addConstr(sell[2] <= inventory[1])
model.addConstr(sell[3] <= inventory[2])

# Warehouse capacity constraints
model.addConstr(inventory[1] <= warehouse_capacity)
model.addConstr(inventory[2] <= warehouse_capacity)
model.addConstr(inventory[3] <= warehouse_capacity)

# Final inventory requirement
model.addConstr(inventory[3] == final_inventory_required)

# Cash flow constraints
model.addConstr(cash[1] == initial_cash + selling_price[1] * sell[1] - purchase_price[1] * buy[1])
model.addConstr(cash[2] == cash[1] + selling_price[2] * sell[2] - purchase_price[2] * buy[2])
model.addConstr(cash[3] == cash[2] + selling_price[3] * sell[3] - purchase_price[3] * buy[3])

# Cash non-negativity is ensured by variable bounds

# Objective: maximize final cash (equivalent to maximizing profit)
model.setObjective(cash[3], GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Purchasing and Selling Strategy:")
    for t in range(1, 4):
        print(f"Month {t}: Buy = {buy[t].x:.2f}, Sell = {sell[t].x:.2f}, "
              f"End Inventory = {inventory[t].x:.2f}, End Cash = {cash[t].x:.2f}")
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {cash[3].x - initial_cash:.2f} yuan")
```
