A candy factory uses raw materials A, B, and C to process three different brands of candies, A, B, and C. It is known that the content of A, B, and C in each brand of candy, the cost of raw materials, the monthly limit of each raw material, and the unit processing fee and selling price of the three brands of candies are shown in Table 1-7.

Table 1-7

| Item            | A               | B               | C               | Raw Material Cost (Yuan/kg) | Monthly Limit (kg) |
|:----------------|:---------------|:---------------|:---------------|:-----------------------------|:-------------------|
| A               | ≥ 60%          | ≥ 15%          |                | 2.00                        | 2000               |
| B               |                |                |                | 1.50                        | 2500               |
| C               | ≤ 20%          | ≤ 60%          | ≤ 50%          | 1.00                        | 1200               |
| Processing Fee (Yuan/kg) | 0.50         | 0.40           | 0.30           |                             |                     |
| Selling Price (Yuan/kg)   | 3.40         | 2.85           | 2.25           |                             |                     |

How many kilograms of each of the three brands of candies should the factory produce each month to maximize the profit?
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Candy_Production_Optimization")

# Sets
raw_materials = ["A", "B", "C"]
products = ["A", "B", "C"]

# Parameters
raw_cost = {"A": 2.00, "B": 1.50, "C": 1.00}
raw_limit = {"A": 2000, "B": 2500, "C": 1200}

processing_fee = {"A": 0.50, "B": 0.40, "C": 0.30}
selling_price = {"A": 3.40, "B": 2.85, "C": 2.25}

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(products, name="Production", lb=0)  # إنتاج كل نوع حلوى (كجم)
y = model.addVars(raw_materials, products, name="RawUsage", lb=0)  # كمية المادة الخام i في المنتج j

# Objective function: Maximize profit
revenue = gp.quicksum(selling_price[j] * x[j] for j in products)
processing_cost = gp.quicksum(processing_fee[j] * x[j] for j in products)
raw_material_cost = gp.quicksum(raw_cost[i] * y[i, j] for i in raw_materials for j in products)

model.setObjective(revenue - processing_cost - raw_material_cost, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Constraints

# Material balance: total raw materials used in each product equals production
for j in products:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(y[i, j] for i in raw_materials) == x[j], name=f"Balance_{j}")

# Raw material availability limits
for i in raw_materials:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(y[i, j] for j in products) <= raw_limit[i], name=f"Limit_{i}")

# Composition constraints

# Product A: A ≥ 60%, C ≤ 20%
model.addConstr(y["A", "A"] >= 0.60 * x["A"], name="Comp_A_A")
model.addConstr(y["C", "A"] <= 0.20 * x["A"], name="Comp_C_A")

# Product B: A ≥ 15%, C ≤ 60%
model.addConstr(y["A", "B"] >= 0.15 * x["B"], name="Comp_A_B")
model.addConstr(y["C", "B"] <= 0.60 * x["B"], name="Comp_C_B")

# Product C: C ≤ 50%
model.addConstr(y["C", "C"] <= 0.50 * x["C"], name="Comp_C_C")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Production Plan (kg):")
    for j in products:
        print(f"Brand {j}: {x[j].X:.2f} kg")
    print(f"\nMaximum Profit: {model.ObjVal:.2f} Yuan")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
