A shoe store employs 5 full-time sales clerks and 4 part-time sales clerks. Their working hours and wage conditions are shown in Table 3.3.

Table 3.3

|  | Monthly Working Hours | Sales Volume (Pairs/Hour) | Wage (Yuan/Hour) | Overtime Pay (Yuan/Hour) |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Full-time | 160 | 5 | 1 | 1.5 |
| Part-time | 80 | 2 | 0.6 | 0.7 |

Each pair of shoes sold earns a profit of 0.3 yuan. The store has set the following goals:

$p_{1}$: Achieve monthly sales of 5500 pairs;

$p_{2}$: Ensure full employment of all sales clerks;

$p_{3}$: Minimize overtime hours.

Try to establish a model for this problem.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB, quicksum

# Create model
model = Model("Shoe_Store_Goal_Programming")

# Parameters
num_full = 5
num_part = 4

full_regular_hours = 160
part_regular_hours = 80

full_sales_rate = 5
part_sales_rate = 2

full_wage = 1
part_wage = 0.6

full_overtime_wage = 1.5
part_overtime_wage = 0.7

profit_per_pair = 0.3
sales_target = 5500

# Decision variables
# Overtime hours per worker type
of = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Overtime_Full")
op = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Overtime_Part")

# Deviational variables for goals
d1_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d1_minus")
d1_plus = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d1_plus")

d2_minus_f = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d2_minus_full")
d2_plus_f = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d2_plus_full")

d2_minus_p = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d2_minus_part")
d2_plus_p = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d2_plus_part")

# Goal 1: Sales target
total_sales = (
    num_full * (full_regular_hours + of) * full_sales_rate +
    num_part * (part_regular_hours + op) * part_sales_rate
)

model.addConstr(total_sales + d1_minus - d1_plus == sales_target, "Sales_Goal")

# Goal 2: Full employment (no idle regular hours)
# Regular hours are fixed, so deviations measure under/over utilization of regular time
model.addConstr(num_full * full_regular_hours + d2_minus_f - d2_plus_f ==
                num_full * full_regular_hours, "Full_Employment_Full")

model.addConstr(num_part * part_regular_hours + d2_minus_p - d2_plus_p ==
                num_part * part_regular_hours, "Full_Employment_Part")

# Goal 3: Minimize overtime
total_overtime = num_full * of + num_part * op

# Priority weights (P1 >> P2 >> P3)
P1 = 1e6
P2 = 1e4
P3 = 1

model.setObjective(
    P1 * d1_minus + 
    P2 * (d2_minus_f + d2_minus_p) + 
    P3 * total_overtime,
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Solution Found:")
    print(f"Overtime hours per full-time clerk: {of.X:.2f}")
    print(f"Overtime hours per part-time clerk: {op.X:.2f}")
    print(f"Total Sales: {total_sales.getValue():.2f}")
    print(f"Sales Shortage (d1_minus): {d1_minus.X:.2f}")
    print(f"Total Overtime Hours: {total_overtime.getValue():.2f}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
