A certain restaurant operates around the clock, and the number of waiters needed in 24 hours is shown in Table 1.1.

Table 1.1

| Time        | Minimum Number of Waiters Needed | Time        | Minimum Number of Waiters Needed |
|:-----------:|:-------------------------------:|:-----------:|:-------------------------------:|
| $2 \sim 6$  | 4                                | $14 \sim 18$| 7                                |
| $6 \sim 10$ | 8                                | $18 \sim 22$| 12                               |
| $10 \sim 14$| 10                               | $22 \sim 2$ | 4                                |

Each waiter works continuously for 8 hours a day. The goal is to find the minimum number of waiters that meet the above conditions and represent this problem as a linear programming model.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Restaurant_Waiter_Scheduling")

# Time periods (4-hour blocks)
periods = ["2-6", "6-10", "10-14", "14-18", "18-22", "22-2"]

# Minimum demand for each period
demand = {
    "2-6": 4,
    "6-10": 8,
    "10-14": 10,
    "14-18": 7,
    "18-22": 12,
    "22-2": 4
}

# Decision variables:
# x[i] = number of waiters starting work at the beginning of period i
x = model.addVars(periods, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="x", lb=0)

# Objective: Minimize total number of waiters
model.setObjective(sum(x[p] for p in periods), GRB.MINIMIZE)

# Constraints: Each period must be covered by waiters who started in this period
# or in the previous period (since each shift lasts 8 hours = 2 consecutive periods)

# 2-6 covered by (22-2) and (2-6)
model.addConstr(x["22-2"] + x["2-6"] >= demand["2-6"], name="cover_2_6")

# 6-10 covered by (2-6) and (6-10)
model.addConstr(x["2-6"] + x["6-10"] >= demand["6-10"], name="cover_6_10")

# 10-14 covered by (6-10) and (10-14)
model.addConstr(x["6-10"] + x["10-14"] >= demand["10-14"], name="cover_10_14")

# 14-18 covered by (10-14) and (14-18)
model.addConstr(x["10-14"] + x["14-18"] >= demand["14-18"], name="cover_14_18")

# 18-22 covered by (14-18) and (18-22)
model.addConstr(x["14-18"] + x["18-22"] >= demand["18-22"], name="cover_18_22")

# 22-2 covered by (18-22) and (22-2)
model.addConstr(x["18-22"] + x["22-2"] >= demand["22-2"], name="cover_22_2")

# Optimize model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Minimum number of waiters needed: {int(model.objVal)}\n")
    for p in periods:
        print(f"Number of waiters starting at {p}: {int(x[p].x)}")
```
