A dairy processing plant uses milk to produce two dairy products, \( A_{1} \) and \( A_{2} \). One barrel of milk can be processed into 3 kg of \( A_{1} \) in 12 hours on Type A equipment or into 4 kg of \( A_{2} \) in 8 hours on Type B equipment. According to market demand, all produced \( A_{1} \) and \( A_{2} \) can be sold. The profit is 24 yuan per kilogram of \( A_{1} \) and 16 yuan per kilogram of \( A_{2} \). The processing plant can get a daily supply of 50 barrels of milk, with a total of 480 hours of labor time available from regular workers each day. The Type A equipment can process up to 100 kg of \( A_{1} \) per day, while the processing capacity of Type B equipment is not limited. Formulate a production plan for the plant to maximize daily profit.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Dairy_Production_Plan")

# Decision variables
# x1: barrels of milk used to produce A1
# x2: barrels of milk used to produce A2
x1 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="x1", lb=0)
x2 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="x2", lb=0)

# Objective function coefficients
# Profit per barrel:
# A1: 3 kg * 24 yuan = 72 yuan
# A2: 4 kg * 16 yuan = 64 yuan
model.setObjective(72 * x1 + 64 * x2, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Constraints

# Milk supply constraint
model.addConstr(x1 + x2 <= 50, name="Milk_Supply")

# Labor time constraint (12 hours per barrel for A1, 8 hours per barrel for A2)
model.addConstr(12 * x1 + 8 * x2 <= 480, name="Labor_Time")

# Type A equipment capacity (max 100 kg of A1 per day, 3 kg per barrel)
model.addConstr(3 * x1 <= 100, name="TypeA_Capacity")

# Optimize model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal barrels for A1 production: {x1.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Optimal barrels for A2 production: {x2.x:.2f}")
    print(f"Maximum daily profit: {model.objVal:.2f} yuan")
