A company blends two types of crude oil (A and B) to produce two types of gasoline (Type I and Type II). The minimum proportion of crude oil A in gasoline Types I and II is 50% and 60%, respectively. The selling prices are 4800 yuan/t and 5600 yuan/t, respectively. The company has current inventories of 500 t of crude oil A and 1000 t of crude oil B, and they can purchase up to 1500 t of crude oil A from the market. The market price for crude oil A is: 10,000 yuan/t for purchases up to 500 t; 8,000 yuan/t for the portion exceeding 500 t but not exceeding 1000 t; 6,000 yuan/t for the portion exceeding 1000 t. How should the company plan its purchasing and processing of crude oil?
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Crude_Oil_Blending")

# Decision variables
x_AI = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x_AI")     # Crude A used in Gasoline I
x_BI = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x_BI")     # Crude B used in Gasoline I
x_AII = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x_AII")   # Crude A used in Gasoline II
x_BII = model.addVar(lb=0, name="x_BII")   # Crude B used in Gasoline II

# Purchase variables for crude A (piecewise pricing)
p1 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=500, name="p1")  # First 500 t at 10000 yuan/t
p2 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=500, name="p2")  # Next 500 t at 8000 yuan/t
p3 = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=500, name="p3")  # Next 500 t at 6000 yuan/t

# Total purchase constraint
model.addConstr(p1 + p2 + p3 <= 1500, name="Total_Purchase_Limit")

# Raw material availability constraints
model.addConstr(x_AI + x_AII <= 500 + p1 + p2 + p3, name="Crude_A_Balance")
model.addConstr(x_BI + x_BII <= 1000, name="Crude_B_Balance")

# Proportion constraints
model.addConstr(x_AI >= 0.5 * (x_AI + x_BI), name="Prop_I")
model.addConstr(x_AII >= 0.6 * (x_AII + x_BII), name="Prop_II")

# Objective function: Maximize profit
revenue = 4800 * (x_AI + x_BI) + 5600 * (x_AII + x_BII)
purchase_cost = 10000 * p1 + 8000 * p2 + 6000 * p3

model.setObjective(revenue - purchase_cost, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Profit:", model.objVal)
    for v in model.getVars():
        print(f"{v.varName} = {v.x}")
