A beverage factory produces a kind of beverage to meet market demand. According to market forecasts, the sales department of the factory has determined the demand for the beverage for the next 4 weeks. The planning department, based on the actual situation of the factory, has provided the production capacity and production cost for the next 4 weeks, as shown in Table 1. When there is a surplus of beverages after meeting the demand each week, a storage cost of 0.2 thousand yuan per week per thousand boxes of beverages needs to be paid. How should the production plan be arranged to minimize the total cost (the sum of production cost and storage cost) over the four weeks while meeting the weekly market demand?

Table 1 Beverage Production and Demand Data:

\begin{tabular}{c|c|c|c}
\hline 
Week & Demand/1000 boxes & Production Capacity/1000 boxes & Cost per 1000 boxes/1000 yuan \\
\hline 
1 & 15 & 30 & 5.0 \\
\hline 
2 & 25 & 40 & 5.1 \\
\hline 
3 & 35 & 45 & 5.4 \\
\hline 
4 & 25 & 20 & 5.5 \\
\hline 
Total & 100 & 135 & \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB, quicksum

# Data
weeks = range(4)
demand = [15, 25, 35, 25]              # Demand (1000 boxes)
capacity = [30, 40, 45, 20]            # Production capacity (1000 boxes)
prod_cost = [5.0, 5.1, 5.4, 5.5]       # Production cost (1000 yuan per 1000 boxes)
hold_cost = 0.2                        # Holding cost (1000 yuan per 1000 boxes per week)

# Create model
model = Model("Beverage_Production_Planning")

# Decision variables
production = model.addVars(weeks, lb=0, name="Production")
inventory = model.addVars(weeks, lb=0, name="Inventory")

# Objective function: Minimize production + holding costs
model.setObjective(
    quicksum(prod_cost[t] * production[t] for t in weeks) +
    quicksum(hold_cost * inventory[t] for t in weeks),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Constraints

# Production capacity constraints
for t in weeks:
    model.addConstr(production[t] <= capacity[t], name=f"Capacity_{t+1}")

# Inventory balance constraints
for t in weeks:
    if t == 0:
        model.addConstr(production[t] - demand[t] == inventory[t], name=f"InventoryBalance_{t+1}")
    else:
        model.addConstr(inventory[t-1] + production[t] - demand[t] == inventory[t],
                        name=f"InventoryBalance_{t+1}")

# No ending inventory required (optional: force to zero if desired)
model.addConstr(inventory[3] == 0, name="EndingInventory")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Total Cost (thousand yuan):", model.objVal)
    for t in weeks:
        print(f"Week {t+1}: Production = {production[t].x:.2f}, Inventory = {inventory[t].x:.2f}")
