A company uses steel and aluminum as raw materials to produce two products (A and B). A single unit of product A requires 6 kg of steel, 8 kg of aluminum, 11 hours of labor, and yields a profit of 5000 yuan (excluding worker overtime pay). A single unit of product B requires 12 kg of steel, 20 kg of aluminum, 24 hours of labor, and yields a profit of 11000 yuan (excluding worker overtime pay). The company currently has 200 kg of steel, 300 kg of aluminum, and 300 hours of labor available. If workers need to work overtime, the overtime pay is 100 yuan per hour. Please develop a production plan to maximize the company's profit and minimize worker overtime.
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Production_Planning")

# Decision variables
A = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Product_A", lb=0)
B = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Product_B", lb=0)
OT = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Overtime_Hours", lb=0)

# Resource constraints
model.addConstr(6 * A + 12 * B <= 200, name="Steel_Constraint")
model.addConstr(8 * A + 20 * B <= 300, name="Aluminum_Constraint")
model.addConstr(11 * A + 24 * B <= 300 + OT, name="Labor_Constraint")

# Objective function: Maximize profit minus overtime cost
model.setObjective(5000 * A + 11000 * B - 100 * OT, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal production of Product A: {A.x:.2f} units")
    print(f"Optimal production of Product B: {B.x:.2f} units")
    print(f"Overtime hours required: {OT.x:.2f} hours")
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {model.objVal:.2f} yuan")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
