In network communication services, bandwidth plays an important role. Below is a bandwidth communication table between several communication nodes, showing the bandwidth between any two nodes. If two nodes cannot be directly connected, the corresponding bandwidth is $0$. It is required to establish a link between node $A$ and node $E$ that must pass through service node $C$ (without loops). The bandwidth of this link is defined as the minimum bandwidth value on the link. Please propose a reasonable link arrangement to maximize the bandwidth of this link and find out the maximum bandwidth.

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|}
        \hline
        & A & B & C & D & E \\
        \hline
        A & 0 & 90 & 85 & 0 & 65 \\
        \hline
        B & 95 & 0 & 70 & 65 & 34 \\
        \hline
        C & 60 & 0 & 0 & 88 & 80 \\
        \hline
        D & 67 & 30 & 25 & 0 & 84 \\
        \hline
        E & 0 & 51 & 0 & 56 & 0 \\
        \hline
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}
-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Nodes
nodes = ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E']

# Bandwidth matrix (directed)
bandwidth = {
    ('A','A'):0, ('A','B'):90, ('A','C'):85, ('A','D'):0,  ('A','E'):65,
    ('B','A'):95, ('B','B'):0,  ('B','C'):70, ('B','D'):65, ('B','E'):34,
    ('C','A'):60, ('C','B'):0,  ('C','C'):0,  ('C','D'):88, ('C','E'):80,
    ('D','A'):67, ('D','B'):30, ('D','C'):25, ('D','D'):0,  ('D','E'):84,
    ('E','A'):0,  ('E','B'):51, ('E','C'):0,  ('E','D'):56, ('E','E'):0,
}

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Maximize_Min_Bandwidth_Path")

# Decision variables: x[i,j] = 1 if arc (i,j) is used
x = model.addVars(bandwidth.keys(), vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")

# Flow variables for path construction
f = model.addVars(bandwidth.keys(), vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, lb=0, ub=1, name="f")

# Minimum bandwidth variable
t = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="t")

# Objective: maximize minimum bandwidth
model.setObjective(t, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Only allow arcs with positive bandwidth
for (i,j), cap in bandwidth.items():
    if cap == 0:
        model.addConstr(x[i,j] == 0)

# Flow conservation constraints
for n in nodes:
    if n == 'A':
        model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(f['A',j] for j in nodes) -
                        gp.quicksum(f[j,'A'] for j in nodes) == 1)
    elif n == 'E':
        model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(f['E',j] for j in nodes) -
                        gp.quicksum(f[j,'E'] for j in nodes) == -1)
    else:
        model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(f[n,j] for j in nodes) -
                        gp.quicksum(f[j,n] for j in nodes) == 0)

# Flow can only pass through selected arcs
for (i,j) in bandwidth.keys():
    model.addConstr(f[i,j] <= x[i,j])

# Ensure path passes through node C
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(f[j,'C'] for j in nodes) == 1)
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(f['C',j] for j in nodes) == 1)

# Link minimum bandwidth to selected arcs
for (i,j), cap in bandwidth.items():
    if cap > 0:
        model.addConstr(t <= cap + (1 - x[i,j]) * 1e5)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Maximum Bandwidth: {t.X}")
    print("Selected Path:")
    for (i,j) in bandwidth.keys():
        if x[i,j].X > 0.5:
            print(f"{i} -> {j} (Bandwidth: {bandwidth[i,j]})")
